pgTitle: List of United States Numbered Highways

rows.text: Maine signs the east end along US 1 several blocks south of I-295
New York signs the north end at a dead end just south of the border crossing
711 The distance between the junctions at West Fargo and Fargo is 5 mi.
Wyoming signs the east (south) end where AASHTO has it join US 14/US 16/US 20 west of Greybull
78 The length of the extension is 14 mi.
123 The length of the old alignment near Wilmington is 8.5 mi.
177 The new length in North Carolina is 4 mi.
75 The new length in Georgia is 17 mi.
703 The distance between the junctions at South Bend and Elkhart is 17 mi.
West Virginia does not sign US 48 yet
Colorado signs the west end at US 160 northeast of Trinidad
1206 The distance between the old and new termini near Pittsfield is 9 mi.
Texas signs the west end at a point east of the border crossing
New York signs the north (east) end in Niagara Falls, northeast of the border crossing
969 The distance between the junctions at Ferriday and Clayton is 6 mi.
Minnesota signs the north end at I-35 south of I-90
Arizona signs the west end at SR 64 in Valle.
South Dakota signs the north end at I-90 at Presho
Texas signs the south end at US 87 northwest of Brady
Wyoming does not sign US 187, but it appears in the 1989 log, completely concurrent with US 191 except for a short piece in Rock Springs
1657 The distance between the junctions at Chambers and Sanders is 6 mi.
Mississippi records indicate the west end is at jct. US 84 in Bude, although there are US 98 shields as far west as Natchez. Florida signs US 98 east of US 1, ending at FL A1A.
Utah signs the north end where AASHTO has it join US 191
